00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,560
It's charity.

296
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:27,780
Can those people be found?

297
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,640
For one, it's been too long.

298
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:33,280
It happened over 20 years ago,

299
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:34,480
and we can't even find a name.

300
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:35,480
As for the other one,

301
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:36,080
he's dead.

302
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,200
Dead?

303
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:41,440
Rumor has it that not long after being sent in,

304
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:43,320
he died unexpectedly of a heart attack.

305
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:45,160
His family even made a scene about it for a while.

306
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:45,880
Later,

307
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:48,220
Lin's Group paid a large sum of money,

308
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:50,040
and the matter was dropped.

309
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:54,520
How about it?

310
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,250
Got your appetite back?

311
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:57,160
Eat up.

312
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,840
I need to go to the sanatorium.

313
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:01,240
We definitely have to go.

314
00:21:01,320 --> 00:21:02,720
Let me check my schedule.

315
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:07,120
Tomorrow, the day after...

316
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,360
Let's bring uncle along the day after tomorrow.

317
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:09,160
I'm going now.

318
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:10,440
No,

319
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,440
you haven't eaten yet.

320
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:18,100
Zhang Chao, right?

321
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:20,080
No visits are allowed today.

322
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:21,320
Why?

323
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:23,440
The patient is receiving special treatment

324
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:25,560
and is currently unable to see anyone.

325
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:27,040
What kind of illness does he have?

326
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:28,720
What special treatment is he receiving?

327
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:29,760
I don't know about that.

328
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:30,360
Next.

329
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:31,520
Wait.

330
00:21:31,680 --> 00:21:33,320
I want to see his attending physician.

331
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:34,560
The attending physician is very busy

332
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:36,040
and has no time to see guests.

333
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:37,120
As the patient's family,

334
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:40,250
I have the right to know Zhang Chao's current condition.

335
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,640
What's wrong with you?

336
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:43,080
Didn't I tell you?

337
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:44,840
No one can see him today.

338
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,320
You don't have a reasonable excuse.

339
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:47,360
Hurry up.

340
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:49,640
Or we can come back another day.

341
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:51,960
No, I must see Zhang Chao today.

342
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:54,240
Please let them know again.

343
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:55,160
No.

344
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:56,840
If you keep interfering with our work, I'll call the police.

345
00:21:56,840 --> 00:21:58,120
But your reason isn't sufficient. No, no, no.

346
00:21:58,120 --> 00:21:58,400
Listen to me, everyone.

347
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,000
Why can't I see him? I'm sorry.

348
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,160
We just care about the patient.

349
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:01,600
Sorry.

350
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,200
Sorry for holding you all up.

351
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:04,720
Let's go.

352
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:05,920
There are so many people here.

353
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:07,160
What are you doing?

354
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:08,420
Listen to me, let's go.

355
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,280
Why did you push me out?

356
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:12,440
Calm down.

357
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:14,840
My patient

358
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:17,040
suffers from severe dissociative identity disorder.

359
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,320
Now he's locked up in there

360
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:19,240
and isn't allowed to see anyone.

361
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:20,640
There must be something wrong.

362
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:21,520
I know there is,

363
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,530
but do we have any evidence?

364
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,860
What did you tell me this morning?

365
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:27,120
Without direct evidence,

366
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:29,250
Old Du can't help us even if he wants to.

367
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:30,200
If you make a scene like this,

368
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,130
can you imagine the consequences?

369
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:34,200
Have you ever thought about how Zhang Chao feels?

370
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:36,000
What if something happens to him in there?

371
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:36,240
Yes.

372
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:37,900
Zhang Chao is very important.

373
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:40,320
But the first person you need to protect is yourself.

374
00:22:40,320 --> 00:22:41,560
Then your patient.

375
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:43,360
Are you that selfish?

376
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:46,520
Chen Rong.

377
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:48,420
We are psychiatrists.

378
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,400
We are not gods.

379
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,800
You have done enough for Zhang Chao.

380
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,720
It's because of Zhang Chao, isn't it?

381
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:56,050
You've never liked him.

382
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:57,840
You've always wanted him to stay away from me.

383
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:59,920
You wish he was locked up in there to fend for himself.

384
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,180
Right? What about you?

385
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,200
Is Zhang Chao really

386
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,520
just a patient to you?

387
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:06,040
Chen Rong,

388
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:07,720
you are a psychiatrist.

389
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,600
You must stay calm at all times.

390
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:10,880
You have to restrain yourself.

391
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:12,280
You can't lose your mind.

392
00:23:12,920 --> 00:23:14,000
Look at yourself now.

393
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,120
Do you still look like a psychiatrist?

394
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:17,600
At a time like this,

395
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,840
what are you saying?

396
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:22,320
I was really wrong about you.

397
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:25,320
I'm sorry. I didn't mean that.

398
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:25,920
I'm just worried.

399
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:26,400
Yes.

400
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:28,320
Zhang Chao is just a patient.

401
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:30,200
A patient you don't really like.

402
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:31,760
But you could never imagine

403
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:32,960
what it feels like

404
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:35,160
to have your patient die in front of you.

405
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:51,170
Do you think you are the only one

406
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:53,080
who has lost someone?

407
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,200
I once had a patient,

408
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:06,120
a 15-year-old girl.

409
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,410
Severe depression.

410
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:11,000
Anorexia.

411
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:14,760
She had attempted suicide three times.

412
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:18,320
I spent two years

413
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:21,500
bringing her back from the edge of death.

414
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:26,520
During your interactions with classmates at school,

415
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:27,980
have you felt any changes?

416
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:34,240
Did you remember something?

417
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:36,160
Your clothes are inside out.

418
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:42,680
During the treatment,

419
00:24:43,320 --> 00:24:45,120
she gradually started to smile.

420
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:48,440
She also showed a willingness to communicate with others.

421
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:50,000
I thought I had cured her.

422
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:53,600
I told her myself,

423
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:54,980
Congratulations.

424
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:57,480
You don't need to come here anymore.

425
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:59,000
She suddenly broke down.

426
00:25:00,320 --> 00:25:01,400
She told me

427
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,210
that she had fallen in love with me.

428
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:08,360
I explained to her what transference is.

429
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:10,440
I told her about the unequal power dynamic

430
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:11,320
between a therapist and a client.

431
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:12,480
None of it worked.

432
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:16,840
I rejected her.

433
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:23,490
After I rejected her for the last time,

434
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:25,880
her mother told me

435
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:29,020
that she had left this world forever.

436
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:32,600
Right in this sea.

437
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:52,240
Then you know what happened.

438
00:25:52,360 --> 00:25:53,560
I closed the clinic.

439
00:25:53,840 --> 00:25:55,970
I come to this sea when I have free time.

440
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:57,800
I reflect on myself.

441
00:25:58,600 --> 00:25:59,640
I did too much.

442
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:02,160
I went far beyond the boundaries

443
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:04,090
between a counselor and a patient.

444
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:05,760
I thought of myself as

445
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:07,240
her only lifesaver.

446
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,130
Unfortunately, she thought the same.

447
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:14,320
So you keep reminding me

448
00:26:15,920 --> 00:26:17,920
to keep my distance from Zhang Chao.

449
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:24,240
A person's last lifesaver

450
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:25,300
cannot be a doctor.

451
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:28,080
Nor can it be their parents,

452
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:28,940
or their lover.

453
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:31,940
It can only be themselves.

454
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:36,340
We need to let them see themselves

455
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:37,960
and understand themselves.

456
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:41,600
Let them grow up again with their own strength.

457
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:43,440
This is our purpose.

458
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:48,480
I'm sorry.

459
00:26:50,120 --> 00:26:52,380
I shouldn't have said that to you before.

460
00:26:55,560 --> 00:26:56,620
How should I put it?

461
00:26:58,400 --> 00:26:59,860
I've already come ashore,

462
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:02,440
but I can always find a grain of sand on my hands,

463
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:03,440
my feet,

464
00:27:03,440 --> 00:27:05,840
my body, and in my backpack.

465
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:09,720
You said I don't understand what Li Weihao means to you.

466
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:11,250
How could I not understand?

467
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:14,180
I just don't want these grains of sand

468
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:16,200
to affect your life too.

469
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:46,840
Before Weihao jumped off the building,

470
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:48,120
he texted me.

471
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:52,920
I didn't realize at all

472
00:27:54,120 --> 00:27:55,720
that it was a farewell.

473
00:27:58,440 --> 00:27:59,480
That day,

474
00:28:00,600 --> 00:28:01,840
I had no work

475
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:04,240
or anything important to do.

476
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:07,360
I was just drinking and chatting with friends.

477
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:13,320
It wasn't until the third day

478
00:28:14,280 --> 00:28:16,540
that I bought a ticket back to Qiongzhou.

479
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:25,240
I still can't accept it even now.

480
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:27,480
My patient,

481
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:29,680
because of my negligence,

482
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:33,450
committed suicide.

483
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:36,280
A life is gone.

484
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:40,960
I am a psychiatrist.

485
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:42,840
I missed a text,

486
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:43,960
a call,

487
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:49,280
and a life is gone.

488
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:58,680
To me, Zhang Chao

489
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:01,040
is not just a patient.

490
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:03,800
He is Weihao's good friend

491
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:06,560
and an extension of Weihao.

492
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:09,320
Something like this,

493
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:13,400
I don't want to go through it again.

494
00:29:20,600 --> 00:29:22,660
Zhang Chao is different from Weihao.

495
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:24,890
Depression starts with giving up.

496
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:27,800
What does dissociation start with?

497
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:32,000
Protection.

498
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:36,000
You have to trust Zhang Chao,

499
00:29:36,360 --> 00:29:38,020
and trust yourself even more.

500
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:40,360
I will always be by your side.

501
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:42,800
I will work hard with you.

502
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:00,800
Cheer up.
